race.comment: The well-related LECONFIELD (3) (half to G2 winner Tuscan Queen) finally shed the maiden tag over this track and trip last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Nicely placed to go back-to-back. PREMIUM STAR (1) has a handy record over this course and distance with two wins and a second from four attempts and get the services of gun hoop Wiggins in the saddle. Shapes as a key contender. INNOVATES (2) saves his best form for his home circuit here and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. In the mix. IT'S BEEN A TREK (4) has only missed a drum once in five starts over this seven-furlong journey and looks one for the exotics players. STARMEIRA (6) best of the rest.
